inn1.comm: swinging into the pads, tapped calmly out to midwicket, and the Dutch are up and running
good delivery holds its line on off stump, squirted out to point with a hint of outside-edge
poor delivery on the pads, flicked firmly through backward square, Bresnan makes good ground on the slide, but parries the ball into the rope
on the line of off, firmly blocked
outside off, not a lot of carry, not much swing either. But left alone
attempted yorker, well dug out and squeezed through the gap in the covers. A very composed start for the Dutch
good line and length, notable pace as well. Left alone
full and straight, defended
pushed back onto the stumps, good attacking line so far
up onto the toes, punched out to the covers.
straying onto the pads, and minnow or not, the Dutch don't miss out there
pushed into the covers to complete the second over of the match. Good progress so far
full and straight, defended back down the pitch
no swing for Jimmy, which suggests there won't be swing for anyone, because he tends to locate it like a wasp to a picnic. Flicked out to midwicket
straight again, tighter lines for England now. Strauss and Anderson have a quick chat as a result. No slips at present
battered! Not quite timed, but the placement was perfect, up and over the infield and into the gap at long-on. Bottom hand is the best hand
Anderson drops his length back, Kervezee responds accordingly
poked into the covers, another single to complete another comfortable over
pushed back into the stumps, defended
banged in short, good delivery in the circumstances, Prior leaps to gather
another short ball, and that's good aggression. Ducked again, but only passes at chest height, so no concern about the length
a fraction of width outside off, pushed down to third man
a bit of width and a wild flash from deep outside leg. No contact
another bouncer, and a maiden from Broad to exercise some control for England. Good over
tucked off the hip, another run
half an appeal as the ball angles towards the leg side. Strikes the pad, but no great enthusiasm
flicked down to fine leg again
worked into the leg side
Bresnan very much targeting the body so far, nudged down into the pitch and another single
outside off this time, and coolly pushed for a single to mid-off, who fields with a dramatic slide
slashed down to third man, a touch of width
dropped! Down the track, a wild squirted edge, goes high and hard past Prior's outstretched left glove. He didn't actually get a hand to it, but should have done
subtle placement! Down the track, an open face, and lifts the ball expertly into the gap at wide third man. No-one there, and that's a brace of boundaries!
pushed onto the back foot, defended out to cover
short, and through to the keeper, who gathers this time
makes room outside leg, and that is sweetly boshed through the covers! Cracking shot, and the Netherlands are giving England plenty to ponder so far ...
smacked up and over midwicket, plugs in the gap beyond two fielders. Perfectly safe
short, swished, top-edged, caught. Esay peasy and that's the end of Kervezee. A sparky innings, but picked the wrong stroke for a ball that didn't get up all that much.
that's not the perfect ball to the new batsman... unless you are the new  batsman of course! A freebie on leg stump, and four easy runs
outside off, lifting through to the keeper
nurdled down to third man, another single
short and sharp, that strikes the shoulder as Barresi recoils. Aggression to finish the over, and the batsman is fine. On we go
slower short ball, die straight, and defended with a hop
defended with a hint of inside-edge, the ball bobbles down into the crease
big stride forward, that ball threatened to bend back in. Defended out to cover
big stride again, pushed out to cover again
excellent bouncer, attacking the helmet. Not much the batsman can do, except not get hit or out. Which he achieved
that is as poor a delivery as the last one was excellent. Short and wide, and slashed fine through third man. Barresi is flying!
climbing onto the toes, fenced down to third man
turned to square leg
good lifter, climbing into Prior's gloves, and just beating the edge
down the track, has a wild waft, and misses
back of a length once again, good areas Bressie
punched out to point off the back foot, tidy work from Bresnan in that over. England exerting a measure of control now
wide on the crease, attacking the base of off. Defended stoutly
good wheels from Broad, outside off, holding its line, and passes the edge
attacking the top of off this time, defended
short, and an attempted swish. No contact
another solid dot ball, probing length from Broad
solid work from Broad, on off stump, and that's a maiden
edged! But no slips. Full outside off, draws the batsman onto the front foot and his drive finds a thick edge which flies through about second slip
on off stump, behind the line and defended to the off side
bouncer, a regular method of attack today, and it's comfortably avoided
tucked off the hip into the leg side
another short ball, drifting down the leg side and pulled away to fine leg. Using the pace on the ball, but the line was poor
worked down to third man so he'll keep the strike
tossed up, ends up being a low full toss and pushed back to the bowler
outside off stump and worked back down to the bowler
tossed up on off stump, neatly worked away through midwicket with a turn of the wrists

Has Swann struck in his first over? Drifts past the edge and Prior whips off the bails. Big appeal and it's gone to the third umpire. This is very close. On the line is out. And he's gone, but in slightly chaotic circumstances as the big screen appears to be broken so the decision is relayed to the on-field umpire
outside off stump, onto the front foot and defended down the pitch
attacking line from Swann outside off and the batsman comes into the front foot to defend
cross-seam to start with, on off stump and nudged into the leg side
goes back into the crease and works this neatly out to deep square
outside off and pushed square on the off side
turned into the leg side, already signs that Colly will be difficult to score off
outside off, ten Doeshcate opens the face but can't beat backward point
pushed square into the covers again and a good start from Collingwood as England claw back the run-rate
on off stump and pushed back to the bowler
some aggression this time with a string drive but it goes straight to mid-off
another drive and this time there's a fumble at mid-off which allows the batsmen to switch ends...that will annoy Swann
tossed up and defended to the off side
almost gets a leading as he looks to turn this into the leg side
angled down to backward point
goes onto the back foot and works this through midwicket...Netherlands can't afford to become bogged down here
back outside off stump this time and pushed firmly into the covers
stands tall and punches down to mid-off
very nice from Collingwood, holds this back a fraction more and ten Doeschate is almost early on the shot as he plays forward
very neat from ten Doeschate as he goes right across his crease then tucks a straight ball down to fine leg...nice use of the wrists, but a good job he didn't miss it
worked off middle stump backward of square on the leg side
another well-placed single into the on side which is what Netherlands need to do
tossed up outside off and driven down to mid-off
touch shorter which allows him to work it off the back foot towards square leg
good push-and-run in this over as another single is worked into the leg side between midwicket and square leg
wider outside off, driven firmly down the ground and that was a very sensible over from Netherlands
taken off about middle stump and worked out to deep square
top shot...dragged down a little short from Collingwood and ten Doeschate is onto the back foot then drives sweetly off the back foot
that's sensible batting to take a single after the boundary
fuller on off stump, pushed into the on side and Collingwood dives across to get a hand on it on his follow through
tucked off the stumps out to deep square and that's sharp running
another sweet drive, well timed but Pietersen makes a diving save moving to his left at mid-off
plenty of air again from Swann and it's whipped down to long on
onto the front foot and opens the face towards backward point...good understanding between these two batsmen
straighter ball outside off and punched back to the bowler
worked off the back foot into the gap at midwicket
fuller on the stumps and it dribbles into the off side
tries to use his feet but ends up yorking himself and can't get the ball away
full on the stumps, hint of something there as it's bunted down to long-on
outside off and chopped away to backward point...didn't bounce too much
nicely flicked away off middle stump out to deep square-leg where Bopara is on duty

on off stump, worked into the leg side...oh, what's happened there? Ian Bell has flung it into the ground towards Prior where it bounces in the footholes and loops over the keeper away for a single. Slightly needless.
worked away down to third man
finds another gap in the off side and Netherlands are playing very calmly at the moment
waits for this one and plays with the turn into the leg side
touch wider outside off and Cooper can't beat midwicket
and again...can't beat the midwicket man as he plays with the turn
slightly quicker outside off and pushed firmly back to Swann
finds a gap this time between square leg and midwicket
pushed through outside off, solid defence back to the bowler to end another tight over
Prior up to the stumps to one of the world's best quicks, blocked back to the bowler
similar fullish length, hint of indrift and and it's punched down the ground
this time ten Doeschate uses the indrift to flick around the corner for a jogged single
shorter length this time from Anderson and Cooper pops up on his toes to drop this to point
we have entered the much-maligned middle overs as this is worked down the ground
attempted late-dab-cut-prod, too close to off stump for the shot really and it bobbles off the edge
ten Doeschate skips down the wicket to Swann's flight but some drop means the batsman can only defend
huge, tempting, almost morally-corrupt flight but ten Doeschate is monastic in his discipline
this time ten Doeschate gets it away, pushing down the ground
Swann operating a long way outside off stump, which usually gets commentators muttering about an 'Australian line', an attempted sweep goes nowhere
carefully defended this time, England look much better with Swann back in their ranks
Cooper pushes a single into space to pinch the strike
Anderson gets his line slightly wrong which allows a routine work-to-leg to pick up a single
wristily driven past the cover point
"ooooh Jimmy boy!" coos Matt Prior. Fair enough really, it was a good indrifting yorker that Cooper did well to bunt down on
this time the single is taken with a mistimed drive to cover, sharp running from this organised pair
100 up for the Netherlands. Good work too, they have been fluent against all but Swann. They get there courtesy of a mistimed cut
uppish, but chip shots are supposed to be. Cooper flicking to a deep mid-on to steal the strike again
starts well, touch of flight, touch of spin, carefully defended
ah the curse of the part-time spinner - the dragged down short ball. Cooper does the business and cuts it away past point to the boundary
this time it's pushed away into a gap for one
ten Doeschate down on one knee and giving this sweep some humpty down to fine leg
good stand this 51 from 73 as Cooper collects a couple driving out to deep cover
productive over ends with careful defence. Netherlands doing the Associates proud here
starts with a real offspinner that ten Doeschate sweeps airily but powerfully to the deep midwicket boundary, one-bounce for four. Looked like he made his mind up to play that shot very early
good response from the bowler, on a length and line and blocked
The Dutchmen are flying now. Sorry. Quality shot though, ten Doeschate opening the face at the last possible moment to glide it to the third-man boundary. This is doing my fantasy team no end of good
ah similarly delicate work to leg, only for one but it looked good
finally a dot-ball respite for Collingwood as Cooper blocks
Cooper walks across his stumps, like a reverse Simon Katich, and flicks this to fine leg
Pietersen continues to doll up some flight and it's driven firmly through a diving short cover
carefully dropped into the leg side
ten Doeschate advances down the track menacingly... but only to defend
bosh! He's given that some humpty! Down the track and got the most gentle of full tosses that he swatted into the stands at long-on
full toss followed by a short ball, KP is giving the full exhibition of part-time spin and ten Doeschate is loving it, crashing this towards the cover boundary
Cooper again steals the strike at the end of the over by dabbing a single to long on
Collingwood tumbles to collect a firm drive
another smart piece of fielding saves runs and Bell slides at short third man to save an open-faced glide
ten Doeschate pops forward to prod a defence. Rare quiet moment of late
ten Doeschate went for a wander outside leg, giving himself room, Collingwood was unperturbed and kept his length and line straight enough  to force a defence
milked down the ground for just a single. Decent job this over from Collingwood
good over ends well with Collingwood diving sharply to his left to save a firm drive
short and a touch wide, hardly the model for medium-pace bowlers, ten Doeschate gets up on his toes to cut wristily to deep third man
England persisting back of a length, you can check out our HawkEye tab to so how often they've pitched up, not sure there are many
similar length and line and Cooper defends off the back foot
slightly slower ball from Bresnan and Cooper turns his hands over the ball to send it to leg
first extra of the innings! Huge news. Slipped down the leg side and it bobbles away

dropped by Pietersen. Tough chance and it was grim cricket. "Village all round," spits Miller. Short ball dragged down the leg side, the pull shot finds a top edge that loops down to fine leg where Pietersen skirts round, dives, thrusts out a hand, which meets the ball only for it to bobble out
gone this time. KP's mistake doesn't cost much. Nothing exceptional really, fullish ball chipped straight to short midwicket. Not spectacular but England will be hugely relieved
pushes his first ball very correctly back to the bowler
with the softest of hands, Zuiderent drops this into the off side for a single
ten Doeschate treating Collingwood like the Sydney Barnes he is and defends very watchfully
more quiet defence, ten Doeschate making sure the 1-brings-2 adage doesn't prove right
ooh, moment of alarm as a single is thought and rethought to Anderson at short midwicket. A direct hit might have been trouble
oops, this is an ugly delivery shoved down the leg side
Zuiderent ghosts a shot before deciding against it
for no apparent reason Zuiderent misses a leg-side prod and it thuds off the pads away to fine leg
Bresnan pitches the ball up! This is actually full! He was almost rewarded as ten Doeschate, startled by the length, hung back and only just stabbed a bat down in time
again this a fuller length and defended watchfully
long, pleading appeal from Bresnan as ten Doeschate squeezed a drive through cover. It was pad first, but struck outside the line
another leg bye bobbles down the leg side for a single. Double this score and we will have a match. Here's Gnasher to tall you more
worked into square leg
on off stump, defended with bat and pad together
uses his feet but can't get the ball away into the leg side

shambles from England! ten Doeschate uses his feet and sends the ball miles in the air, but Pietersen and Anderson leave the catch to each other and it falls embarrassingly in the middle of them both. That was awful
pushed back to the bowler
and there's his fifty, reached with a tuck into the leg side and that's an excellent innings from Netherlands' key batsman
hint of movement back into the batsman who pushes into the off side
worked into the leg side
can't find a gap in the off side, but ten Doeschate knows he needs to bat out the innings after getting that life
short ball angled into the body and shovelled into the leg side
full on off stump, driven into the ground and Bresnan sticks a hand out in his follow through
We have a review. Zuiderent is cut in half by Bresnan and England are convinced there's an inside edge. Looks like back leg on replays and he survives. Good decision from Asad Rauf
onto the back foot and worked into the leg side
leans forward and defends into the off side
expansive drive this time but he can't beat Ian Bell at cover
this time he flicks straight to midwicket
gone, Swann makes another breakthrough. Zuiderent never got going today, unlike 15 years ago, and chips a simple catch to midwicket as he tries to find the gap
on off stump and he leans forward to defend his first ball
tight on off stump, a walking defensive push can't beat the bowler
nicely timed square drive off the back foot but doesn't beat backward point
angling into the batsman and it's worked nicely past midwicket to bring up Netherlands' 150...the best effort by an Associate so far in this tournament
opens the face but can't beat backward point
dropped in short and pulled away through midwicket
back of a length on off stump and defended square into the covers
tossed up nicely outside off stump and a leading edge goes along the ground to cover
beat outside off stump, Prior takes the bails off but ten Doeschate's foot is firmly behind the line
dropped into the covers and that's well run
ah, that's a very neat paddle to get the ball through short fine-leg...Broad uses his boot, that's very 1980s, to prevent the boundary
very full, dug out back to the bowler
top shot, superb use of the feet and a flick of the wrists sends this over deep midwicket...this has been a classy innings
back of a length on off stump and de Grooth blocks into the covers
well bowled, de Grooth is beaten outside off as he tries to guide down to third man
nice back-foot drive, stands tall and punches it wide of the cover fielder and the sweeper has work to do
another nice back-foot drive, this time it goes square out to the sweeper
short of a length, he tries to find space on the leg side but Broad is quickly onto it in his follow through
hops back in the crease and nudges a single into midwicket and keeps the strike which is ideal for Netherlands
worked from outside off wide of short fine-leg
that's brilliant from de Grooth, brings out a very fine reverse sweep which races to the third-man boundary...clever batting
pushed in fuller outside off
touch wider and pushed square to backward point
goes for another reverse sweep but this time is taken on the pad
defends with bat and pad together to see out Swann's final delivery of the match
full toss on leg stump but it only costs a single as it's flicked straight to deep square
short ball and it take de Grooth's glove as he tries to pull but falls well short of Prior
opts for another short one and this time de Grooth connects well and finds the gap between deep square and long leg
fuller on off stump, defended back to the bowler
that's a cracking pull, uses Broad's pace and bisects the two fielders in the deep...a valuable innings from de Grooth to give Netherlands the kick they needed
worked off the stumps and that's a decent over for the Dutch
a cutter outside off, pushed towards short third-man
onto the front foot but can't find a gap in the off side
places this one just wide enough of cover
clever again from de Grooth, scoops this through short fine-leg...Netherlands are standing face-to-face with England, it's great to see
this time he drives a full ball through the covers
tight on middle and off and ten Doeschate pushes out to cover
on off stump and pushed back to the bowler
beaten outside off by one that bounces a touch more
worked into midwicket and it's a well taken quick single...ten Doeschate needs as much of the strike as possible
down the leg side, superb take from Prior and a big appeal. Not given by Rauf. Will they review? Nope, and it's a good call as it clipped the pad
worked out through midwicket
big appeal from Anderson...looked like it was going down and again Strauss won't use a review. Didn't appeared very straight.
carefully blocked back to the bowler

who needs a Powerplay!? ten Doeschate spots the (even) slower ball and calmly steps down the wicket and smashes powerfully over the long-on rope. Lovely shot, fetched it from outside off with a flick of the wrists
this time he gets deep into his crease and flicks a single to leg
de Grooth doing just the right thing and picking off a single to get Sachin ten Doeschate back on strike
England have been ragged in the field all day and again they've fluffed a stop as ten Doeschate turned this towards fine leg where some indecision in the fielding allows them to come back for two
ooh, Collingwood is lucky to get away with this. Waist-high full toss asking to be beaten, ten Doeschate picked out fine leg though. Still, the single brings up a 49-ball 50 stand
shorter from Anderson here and it's skims off the edge down to third man
big appeal from Anderson as he finds the pads. Was heading down though
poor delivery, lucky it didn't cost more, full toss down the leg side and it was turned down to fine leg
again the line is wrong - slipping down the leg side - and de Grooth swings it away down to Swann at fine leg who skirts round to field well
short ball, not deliberate, just dragged down. It sat up waiting for punishment and ten Doeschate thwacked it through midwicket, sending it skimming to the rope
two more as again Anderson ventures leg side, ten Doeschate has supple wrists and flicked away. He looks in complete control at the moment
after that long, long wait Broad shoves down a slower ball that de Grooth swings hard at, but misses. Prior fumbled the take and allowed a bye. Broad was less than amused
full and straight this time and not much ten Doeschate can do but flick down the ground. Some very swift running allows him to get back for two
slower delivery again, this time fuller and ten Doeschate plays a very correct check-drive to pick off another single. Mighty innings this

looked, well sounded, like an edge here as de Grooth gave himself room to try and smack the life out of it through cover. Slower ball though and it bounced through to Prior. Batsman guilty of trying to do too much here
that's what the Powerplay can do. de Grooth gives himself plenty of room and tries to dispatch a yorker. It was too full, too straight and crashed into the base of middle
full and straight again and Borren sensibly gets into line to push down to long-on for one
he starts well, back of a length around off stump and Borren plays and misses a run-to-third-man
that's all Borren needs to do, swap the strike back to ten Doeschate. Pushing this full ball down the ground
poor delivery and ten Doeschate cashed in! Slower bouncer dragged leg side, ten Doeschate waited, waited again and then picked a gap fine of a square fine leg and pulled for four

shot! Best of the lot and England will be worried now! Full ball is met with a fuller face as he drives powerfully, timing it perfectly to beat mid-off and take him within a six of a World Cup century
Bresnan's response is to bang it in short and ten Doeschate is up on his toes to drop a single to the leg side
Strauss gives Borren a single with the off-side fielders hanging on the inner circle, fullish ball that Borren pops to point for one
ideal again from Borren, gets the danger man on strike by dropping a shortish ball into the off side for one
ooh, he deserves some luck and has found it here! Short ball and the pull shot found a looping top edge that plopped safely into space

hundred for ten Doeschate and what an innings! 103 off 98 balls, Associate cricket back alive and well! Gets there  by flicking a sharp single to short fine leg, throw comes in and cannons off the stumps before running away for four. Is he the first batsman to reach a World Cup hundred with a five?
Borren is proving an ideal foil, happily letting ten Doeschate do the work by picking off singles
England rocking here! ten Doeschate is on fire! Poor ball, short and sat up, ten Doeschate clumped it and it rocketed between two fielders deep on the leg side
he keeps the strike by bunting a full ball down the ground
full from  the new bowler - Anderson - and flicked into the leg side. ten Doeschate looks to be in some trouble with cramp possibly
worked away into space for a single
oh dear, England really shabby now, high full toss - too high in fact - and swung into the leg side
dinked away to short fine leg. It came off the bat but England wanted to review it. Didn't need HotSpot to prove that came off the bat!

this is horrid. Anderson has lost it here. Another high full toss - beamer - and it came off a flurry of bat and arms to run away for four. Anderson could be taken out of the attack here for bowling beamers, there is some chat with the umpire but he's allowed to continue
this is short and a touch wide, cut to point for a sharp single
with the yorkers going awry Anderson has opted to bang it in and Borren calmly glides to third man
another flick of the wrists from ten Doeschate finds space. Fetching a full ball from outside off to send it hurrying to the midwicket boundary where some desperate, diving fielding saves a couple
Borren has walked a long way outside leg to try and heave this into the off side. Doesn't time it well but gets the single he wanted
this is smashed straight to cover, either side it might have been four
Borren for once not doing what he should be. Gets too clever here and tries to Dilscoop over the keeper and misses
this time Borren finds the single, crunching an ugly cut shot to point
full and straight and even in this mood ten Doeschate can only pick up a single, swishing to leg
poor delivery brings a sharp chance to Trott at short fine leg but it's dropped. It was full and down the leg side and the sweep shot was parried away by a diving Trott.
Anderson continues and aims full, ten Doeschate walked a long way outside leg and the bowler followed him. Prior fumbled the take and allowed a bye
full once more from Anderson, good delivery, and it's run down to third man

ooh, ten Doeschate tries to do too much here, aiming a Dilscoop but there are problems here for him as he takes the single. Really pulls up, stretching his leg - he's had  calf injuries before so let's hope it's just cramp
ah lovely shot! Poor delivery from Anderson, too short and Borren hangs leg side to lift it over short third man for four
and again! Top cricket from Borren, shocking from England. Short and wide once more, Borren  waits leg leg side and thumps it over short third man

four more! Borren on fire! Oh the Ashes must feel a long way away for Anderson. This time he goes full and Borren, simple as you like, stands still and clumps it back over the bowler's head for four. 15 from the over!

all over for ten Doeschate but it's been one of the great minnow innings. Just got under a short ball and spooned it down to Bopara on the square-leg boundary but a fabulous knock that has put Netherlands in with a real chance of an upset
short, shoved down the leg side. Lucky there wasn't a bat on this or it would probably have skirted away for four
Broad is smiling, but he doesn't mean it. Short ball, Borren jumps leg side and top edges a cut that sails over Prior's head and bobbles over the boundary

finally Broad goes full and straight and he's rewarded again with a wicket. Borren giving himself room but it wasn't short so his attempted flay never got near. Excellent cameo knock though from the captain. Hold on, what's going on here!? Borren has stopped going off and he's survived! England only had three inside the circle so it's a no ball! Dear oh dear, the wheels are off and England are a shambles. Collingwood is the offending man, failed to walk in into the circle at midwicket.
Second life for Borren and he this time bunts a single to cover
two more, scoreboard rattling, England revisiting all their World Cup nightmares here!
full and straight and just a single jabbed out this time
fullish again and it's worked away to deep backwards square for a couple more. Broad's bowling duty ends but England might need his batting here!
wow, 12 for effort but just a couple for result. Length ball that Bukhari tried to muller, it was mistimed and plopped into space short of long-on
dear, dear me. England fans look away now. Absolute shocker as Swann drops a sitter at third man. The World Cup is up and running and England are a mess again. This is what Associates are here for!
this time it's swung hard to deep midwicket for a scampered couple
dot ball! Precious, rare dot ball as Borren swishes and misses at a slower ball
shin high full toss is swung into the leg side
yorker to finish is blocked away. Good end to an embarrassing display.

inn2.comm: outside off, a touch of swing, and Strauss flashes outside off
on the pads, you can't bowl there with fine leg up ...
zoinks ... two in two for Strauss, but that could have been played on ... an under-edged cut bounces past off stump!
good delivery, full length, a touch of movement, beats the edge
aggressive drive from Strauss, but sharp fielding at point cuts off the run
wrong line from Bukhari, Strauss taps another boundary wide of short fine leg, and he's up and running
no, he will not need such patience! A calm strike through the covers, and that's a maiden four as an international opener
full again, and driven to short cover
outside off stump and a bit of a loose flash at that one. Gets away with it
big stride forward and defended back down the track
outside off once again, not a lot of carry in that delivery. Left alone
drilled into the covers for another single
clipped into the gap at midwicket
Strauss returns the strike
firm drive, but good line and length from Bukhari. Pietersen has to go straight, and hits the bowler in his followthrough
misdirected, and flicked firmly off the pads to deep midwicket
clipped in front of square, good firm strokeplay from Pietersen, getting onto the front foot at every opportunity
Strauss stays in his crease to work off the hip, but straight to square leg
another well-struck flick, but midwicket intercepts

now that's the way to do it, onto the front foot, and a presumptuous steer in front of square on the leg side. Almost a flamingo flick, but the back leg didn't quite kick up as it used to. Oh well, still four
drilled! That was four all the way, but it deflected off middle stump and away to mid-on
pushed to midwicket
cracked into the covers, he is timing it well today. But straight at the fielder this time
too much width, Pietersen waited a split-second, then caressed a wristy cut in front of point.
Strauss goes up onto his toes to cut, but can't time the stroke as cover intercepts
another cut, again not timed, but a fumble ensures a single
another firm flick. Midwicket is in place once again
slightly back of a length, though Pietersen is still on the front foot. Mistimed drive rolls out to mid-on
down the track, he's feeling the power now. Good work at midwicket saves the run
nearly scuds one through KP's defences, but he jams the bat down late to work a single through square leg
worked to midwicket once again
the keeper is up to the stumps now - a good move -  as KP stands up in his crease to push out to cover
dragged down, and Pietersen is onto it in a flash. Yet again on the front foot, and brutalised through midwicket
driven hard back to the bowler
blocked on the front foot. An authoritative defensive shot, as it happens
cut once again to point, Strauss isn't quite timing that stroke on this pitch
stands tall in the crease and works a single to midwicket
worked off the pads again
driven hard, back to the bowler. KP is hitting the field a lot in his innings so far...
red-bull run! The fielder was back on the edge of the circle, so Pietersen sprinted an instant single to mid-off. Made it in time
bosh. Strauss's determination to hang back in the crease pays dividends as Bukhari drops short. Well pulled through midwicket
outside off, a hint of swing, and Pietersen lets it pass by with a quizzical raise of the bat
woomph. That was travelling. A catchable height as Westdijk thought for a split-second about sticking out his left hand, but valued his digits more than a wicket
full again, met on the front foot. Inevitably
an uppish drive, a few men lurking for that shot, but he plays it well enough, into the covers
driven on the up to a tumbling point. Slightly sliced stroke
driven back down the track
flicked off the toes, through midwicket
cut into the covers, again not timed especially well
back into the crease, tucked out to midwicket
tossed out wide, and KP was reaching as he inside-edged past his stumps. A bit dicey ...
on the pads, a regulation clip through square leg
oops, they've dropped behind now
outside off, no stroke offered
loopy delivery, on a good line and watchfully blocked
punched out to point
steered to point from deep in the crease. Unusually for KP
blocked on the line of off stump
a scampered single to mid-on, that's the end of the first Powerplay
worked away for another single
pushed off the back foot into the leg side
touch short and Strauss pulls it through midwicket
pushed down the leg side, Pietersen overbalances as he tries to flick it away but the keeper can't take it cleanly
full outside off, driven firmly down to mid-off and another scampered single from Pietersen
worked neatly off the pads backward of square and Strauss has to get his skates on get back after needing to avoid Pietersen...but he gets back with a stretch
trademark Strauss this time as he rocks back and cuts this through cover...just a hint of width, but that's his strength
back of a length, pushed down towards mid-off and this time there's not single on offer
stands leg-side of the ball and drives powerfully but straight at cover
slower ball on leg stump, gets to Pietersen on the full and he flicks it out to deep square
comes across the crease and flicks this from middle and off out to midwicket
poor line outside leg stump, easy pickings for Strauss as he flicks it past short fine-leg...the captain continues to score at well in excess of a run-a-ball
same line, same shot, same result...another freebie boundary for Strauss who has looked in fine touch. Turns his wrists and sends it racing to deep square
down the leg side again, everyone misses it and that's five to England's total...tough for the keeper when he's stood up to the stumps
back outside off, driven firmly but straight at cover
pushed into the leg side
full on middle, Pietersen punches with timing but picks out mid-on
hint of width and it's driven square through covers out to the sweeper
another floaty ball on leg stump and Strauss will tuck into them all day (or night) as he collects another boundary to the vacant fine-leg area
wide outside off, chopped into the ground and it bobbles towards short third-man
angled down the leg side, takes the pad and bobbles into the off side
not much bounce and it's worked out to midwicket
uses his feet and then works it along the ground wide of midwicket
down the pitch straight away, doesn't make contact and is taken on the pad but well outside the line of off stump
uses his feet again and pushed back to the bowler
drives with an open face down to long-off
starts on off stump and defended
full on middle and off, worked through midwicket but mid-on makes the save
big full toss on off stump but Strauss can only biff it back to the bowler
another full toss and again Strauss misses out as he drives straight to cover
chopped away through the off side
dropped down short and that's too easy for Strauss as he leans back and hammers it over midwicket
round the wicket, down the pitch and Pietersen flicks it through midwicket
dragged down towards leg stump, worked out to deep square and that takes Strauss to his fifty from 34 balls...a good innings
pushed down to mid-on by KP on the walk
that's poor, pushed down the leg side and Strauss doesn't make contact and the keeper misses another...extra ball for that
pushed into the leg side
short outside off, Strauss drives square on the off side and races for a quick single which has him sprinting for the line
big appeal, KP is struck full on the pad but he's a long way down the pitch and Rauf says not out...Borren doesn't bother with a review
very full on middle, where England didn't bowl enough, and it's dug out into the off side
driven straight to cover
on middle and off, Strauss nearly gets a leading edge as he tries to work into the leg side
back of a length outside off and pushed down to mid-off
offered width and he connects well but picks out backward point
full on leg stump, tucked down to fine leg to bring up England's 100...a good start for this new pair
down the pitch and a lovely, flowing cover drive from Strauss which gives long-off plenty of work
now he brings out the reverse sweep, which has caused him some problems, and gets it fine of short third-man
taken from outside off and worked down to long-on
gone! And it's a left-arm spinner again. What a moment for Pieter Seelaar. Tossed up nicely and Pietersen comes forward to drive but wasn't quite at the pitch and gave a catch to cover
very full and driven straight to cover, but not in the air like KP...to be fair, it was fuller
pushed back to the bowler
full on off stump, driven out to cover
bunted off the back foot down the ground
driven off a thick inside edge towards midwicket
not much bounce on this one as Trott jabs it into the covers to get off the mark
driven down to long-off
full on the stumps and the field is up for Trott so his drive finds mid-on
pushed through outside off and left alone
tossed up this time and flicked through midwicket
gives himself a bit of room to try and drive but only gets it back to the bowler
width outside off and cut away to the cover sweeper
short on off stump but pulled straight to midwicket
width outside off, cut away through the covers and placed well enough for a brace
full and straight from RTD and pushed Trott-like back to the bowler
full toss, not as high as Anderson's collection earlier, and slapped down to fine leg
driven hard down to deep point
this is carefully defended, England just rebuilding for a moment
shortish ball and Strauss somehow manages to wheel away a pull
touch wide from the bowler, close to being a wide in fact, Strauss missed a cut
touch of flight, good line too and Trott milks down the ground
carefully prodded to the leg side
Strauss skips down the wicket and drops to long-on
carefully defended back to the bowler
Trott mistimes a drive and is rewarded with a single to point
Strauss turns his wrists over the ball to send it to deep midwicket
good line, no pace on the ball and not much off the bat either
ten Doeschate drifts leg side and Strauss picks off a single behind square
Trott tries to run this down to third man but it's too close to him, the bottom edge gets the desired effect though and Trott jogs a single
this is very correctly punched back to the bowler
Strauss opens the face on a drive to find a gap at cover
Trott shuffles across his stumps to work a straightish ball into the leg side
tossed-up offspin, Trott watches it onto the face of the bat and pushes a single to long-on
too short here and Strauss rocks back to cut to deep point. Ambles a single
Trott this time rotates the strike by fiddling into the leg side
high-quality milking from Strauss, opening the face to find a gap at deep cover and running swiftly to turn one into two
this is a touch shorter and the cut shot finds point
given a chance to repeat the shot Strauss clears the point fielder this time to pinch the strike
ooh, a shortish ball scuttles under Strauss's attempted cut and it bobbles off the keeper's gloves
Trott loves nothing more than picking off forgettable singles. Well, he probably does but he's awfully good at these
Strauss this time drives out to deep cover
short ball is pulled, without much power, straight to midwicket
good, Collingwood-eque stuff from RTD, Trott flicks a legside single
another legside flick, this time from Strauss, to the fine-leg area where he's made so many today
tossed up high from Cooper and Strauss pats it down to long-off
singles being taken at will here, Trott turns his wrists over the ball to send it to the leg side
Strauss gets deep into his crease to punch this into the leg side. Smart running makes it two
and again the strike rotates, this looks a touch too easy, Strauss works to long-on
short ball is cut straight to point. Trott missed out there
ooh, my fantasy team was almost in jeopardy here as Trott aims - and misses - an attempted hoik to leg
touch leg side from RTD and it's turned around the corner
Trott leans forward and clips a couple to deep midwicket
England look for two and Trott clips down to fine leg, but only one available
for once Strauss mistimes a cut shot and it dribbles out to point
fullish and driven down the ground for another milky single
decent lines from ten Doeschate but no great threat and Trott cruises another single to long-on. Half way to their target now
Trott gets down on one knee and reverse-dabbles a couple
another reverse-sweep! This time met on the full and it goes finer, running away for four, the first boundary of this partnership
driven out to deep point this time
slapped out square of the wicket
patted back to the bowler quietly
that makes it an excellent over for England, Trott's cover drive is always excellent and this half-volley is driven firmly to the ropes
all very easy at the moment, none of the frenzy of before. Strauss leans into a square drive and scampers two
this fiddle to leg came off the bottom of the bat but the bad timing allowed Strauss to hare back for a second
driven without great timing straight to cover
back of a length and Strauss cuts hard but again finds the fielder
misfield stops this from being a hat-trick of dots. Strauss patting carefully to extra cover
Trott keeps the strike with a middle-over push down to long-on
new bowler looks much the same sort of package as the last and Trott pushes a single to cover

the change of bowling does the trick! Strauss, inexplicably, tried to smack this pull shot out the ground and got under it too much, ended up spooning down towards the square leg boundary where Cooper hared in to take the catch. Good innings from Strauss but ends short of hundred
Trott gets a grubber and he's hanging on the back foot. Causes all sorts of ooohs and aaahs
no alarm this time, just a routine single worked into the leg side
Bell gets forward to drive his first ball stylishly to mid-off
touch too wide allows Bell to get off the mark, cutting down to third man
full outside off, nicely driven by Bell wide of mid-off
width outside off and angled down to third man
worked off middle stump through midwicket
comes forward and defends to cover
flicked from middle and off, there's a fumble at midwicket but they decide against the single
opens the face to backward point and they get the quick single...decent comeback from Loots
outside off stump and pushed off the back foot into the covers
driven straight down to mid-on
worked off the stumps to midwicket...good to see the fielders saving singles, trying to build pressure
dragged down short and pulled through midwicket
down the leg side, flicked away sweetly but he can only get a single as long leg does the work
full and driven back to the bowler who doesn't stop it cleanly but it won't cost anything
plenty of width and driven firmly but straight to keep cover
angled towards leg stump and pushed down to long on
well bowled, tight on off stump and Trott can't find a gap
pushed from outside off down to long-on
pulled down short and Bell helps it through square leg, placing it between two fielders
behind the line and defends
angled down the leg side from round the wicket, Trott flicks it out to deep square
nicely bowled on middle, Bell defends to the leg side
tries to work it into a gap at cover but can't get it away
gives himself a little bit of room so he can drive through the off side and places it wide of long-off
backs away to leg and places this through the covers again, a fumble by the sweeper makes it an easy couple
can't place this one past the fielder
on off stump and pushed down the pitch
flicked from outside off towards midwicket who parries it away for a single
touch shorter and Bell waits on the back foot before working it down the ground
walks into this shot but only pushes it back to the bowler
fuller and punched down to long-on
good save at cover, that was well-timed drive from Bell but it only brings a single
driven firmly off the back foot out to the cover sweeper
worked away from middle stump down to long leg...Trott loves the leg side
gives himself room and slashes this one away square past point for a useful boundary...been a while since England had found the rope, helps keep things under control
punched very straight back down the pitch and mid-off scurries around
doesn't time this one as he pushes off the back foot...came off the bottom of the bat
very short outside off and Bell misses out as he flat-bats it towards mid-off
full on off stump, driven back to the bowler in his follow through
opens the face and finds third man
can't beat point as he opens the face and drives
driven again and again straight to the fielder...this time at cover
touch shorter which allows Bell to work it off the body out to deep square-leg
driven straight to mid-off but he's fairly deep and it allows a quick single
driven down the on side, the bowler dives but helps it away for a run
goes for a reverse sweep but only gets a bottom edge into his pad which dribbles away
well, plenty happened that ball...there was a big appeal for lbw but it was sliding down leg, then the ball was thrown in at hit the stumps and bounced away for a single
gives himself a touch of room and drives off the back foot through cover
tossed up and comes out as a juicy full toss...should have gone for four but instead it's a couple wide of long-on to take Trott to another one-day fifty
worked away out to deep midwicket
hint of movement into the batsmen but it's easily pushed down to long on
on leg stump and flicked out to deep square
nicely helped away by Trott, was angled towards the leg side and he swivelled on the shot which easily beat long leg
driven straight to cover
goes for a pull but gets a toe-end into his leg and finds a single to short third-man
worked from outside off down to long-on
uses his feet and drives powerfully inside-out along the ground through cover...brings up the fifty stand
down the pitch again but this time can't beat the bowler
nicely bowled, fired in at leg stump and it cramps Bell for room
tossed up on middle this time and worked down to long-on
stays in his crease and works it through midwicket...excellent placement again from Trott
waits on the back foot again, and it's another couple between long-on and deep midwicket. Very smart, controlled batting
very wide delivery to start, a long way outside off, Bell stretched and stretched to just about toe-end this, fetching it to mid-on. Cricket at it's finest there

wow! That is an absolute stunner from Barresi! So sharp! Trott aimed to flick a delivery that was sliding down the leg side, overbalanced and before he could even think about what had happened, Barresi had the bails off. It was a wide too, remarkable stuff
starts well enough, getting back in his crease to work to leg
Bell picks off a single, working past midwicket
Collingwood aims a back-foot drive and mistimes it horridly and it barely dribbles off his blade
vintage Collingwood! Nudged single to leg
oops, misfield at cover means Bell's gentle drive earns a single it shouldn't have
ooh, how has this got through? Yorker finds a bottom edge, goes through the legs and past the stumps, past the keeper too
shovelled into the leg side for a couple, neatly done
full and on the pads, Collingwood just needed to pierce the infield but picked out a diving short midwicket

with all the fielders on the off side this kind of deliver - short and down the leg side - is criminal. Luckily for Bukhari, Collingwood couldn't get hold of a pull  and it scraps away down the leg side
poor ball, short, wide, sitting up and asking for trouble. Bell, the menacing beast, is trouble and creamed it to the point boundary
much better delivery but the damage is done. Full, straight and patted down the ground
this sticks in the pitch a touch and as a result Bell's punched drive down the ground is a touch uppish. Not that it matters because the bowler can't reach it
good delivery, aimed full and at the stumps, Collingwood squeezes it to midwicket
Bell gives himself room to unfurl a back-foot drive, well timed, but straight to cover
Bell gets a single, but only just. Plenty of yes, no, wait, no, yes, but no need for a 'sorry' as Bell scampers through despite a direct hit
Collingwood unfussily gets a single away into space
Well, well, well. That might just change things. ten Doeschate can do nothing wrong. Bell's 'almost' ODI career continues as he gives himself room to drive, misses and gets bowled
shortish delivery that Collingwood aims a heave at, his form is still some way from vintage and it dribbles off an inside edge
wrong line from Bukhari and precious runs for England. Full and sliding down leg, Collingwood only needs his favourite inside edge and it speeds away to the rope
again this is mistimed off the inside half of the bat but a single will do England well enough
this keeps a touch low and Bopara is rooted to the crease. Plays around his front pad in defence
Bukhari can't seem to get the ball on off stump, again he slides down leg and with a flick of the wrists, Bopara is off the mark
Collingwood is less wristy but he leg-side bunt is even more effective here, collecting a couple to deep square. Bukhari, needless to say, was too far down the leg side
flurry of arms and legs in delivery it ends up slowish and straight and Bopara defends
Bopara drives straight to cover and hares off for a tight single
slower ball, gosh this really was slow. Well executed legcutter and Collingwood was through his stoke a few times before the ball arrived
that will do nicely! Another slower ball but this  time Collingwood read it and swatted that rearrest of beasts - an offside Collingwood boundary, over mid-off
back to single mode, pushed into space
Bopara keeps the strike by languidly driving this down to mid-on
Bopara aims a back-cut, plays it firmly but straight to the short third man
this time it's fuller and pushed down the ground easily
Collingwood down the wicket, aims a horrible heave and it's that staple of Collingwood knocks - the inside edge - that saves him as it skims this far past leg stump
blocked by Bopara to mid-on, pressure building
this time Bopara gets a single, down the wicket and patting to long-on
Collingwood keeps the strike by bunting this out to deep square
ah, that's the Collingwood England love. Nerveless, down on one knee and dinking a paddle sweep past short fine leg for four
aims another one, but this was a long way outside off stump so he didn't have the angle on his side. In the end it bobbles off the knee into the off side
Bopara walks down the ground and gets an inside edge that runs into the long-on region, Bopara was back for a second but needed a full-length dive to get back into his ground
Bopara is eyeing up the leg side and aims a wristy chip that sails down towards long-on, looked horrid half-way but bounced short of the man
full and on the pads, rare good timing means Collingwood can only have a single here as it speeds out to long-on
ooh, hint of leading edge as Bopara tries to work to leg. Ends up heading down to long-off and Bopara jogs through to keep the strike
boot saves four here! Bopara nailed a straight drive and Seelaar shoved out a left foot to save the boundary
excellent work from Collingwood, stands tall to sort of reverse-tap this, took it from well outside leg and almost sent it down to the third man rope, really well timed
top bowling from Seelaar here. Bopara running down the wicket and it was fired flat and down the leg side, would have been a stunning take but technically a missed stumping I suppose
another leading edge, squirts out to the off side
Collingwood running down the wicket this time and managing to shove this to long-on
Bopara again happy to wander down at Seelaar, who shoves through a quicker ball and with soft hands Bopara dabs a couple wide of long-on
this time Bopara stays in his crease and nudges a single into the midwicket region. England almost there now
Bopara has seen enough! Gets a fullish delivery and backs himself to beat the long-off fielder. Aims a fluid drive and nails it, sails flat over the man and over the ropes
good delivery - full and straight - Bopara bunts it down the ground, scampers a couple to take England within one shot of the match. In comes the field...
Bopara finishing it in a rush. Running at the bowler and smacking a waist-high full toss to the midwicket boundary. Scores level now

that's it. Bopara finishes it in style, hoiking this to the midwicket rope to take England home with eight balls to spare. Netherlands were fantastic with the bat and Borren and ten Doeschate sink to their knees now, at the half-way stage they would have been dreaming of glory
